East Asia is the eastern subregion of Asia, which can be defined in either geographical or ethno-cultural terms. Geographically and geopolitically, the region constitutes of China, Hong Kong, Macao, Mongolia, North Korea, South Korea, Japan, and Taiwan. The East Asian states China, North Korea, South Korea, and Taiwan are all unrecognized by at least one other East Asian state. Hong Kong and Macau are officially highly autonomous but are under effective Chinese sovereignty.